[0.010, "o", "\u001b[1;2H\u001b[59X\u001b[2;3HThis is the main Apache HTTP server configuration file.  It contains the\u001b[3;3Hconfiguration \u001b[30m\u001b[103md\u001b[m\u000firectives that give the server its instructions.\u001b[4;2H See <URL:http://http\u001b[30m\u001b[103md\u001b[m\u000f.apache.org/\u001b[30m\u001b[103md\u001b[m\u000focs/2.4/> for \u001b[30m\u001b[103md\u001b[m\u000fetaile\u001b[30m\u001b[103md\u001b[m\u000f information.\u001b[5;2H In particular, see \u001b[6;2H <URL:http://http\u001b[30m\u001b[103md\u001b[m\u000f.apache.org/\u001b[30m\u001b[103md\u001b[m\u000focs/2.4/mo\u001b[30m\u001b[103md\u001b[m\u000f/\u001b[30m\u001b[103md\u001b[m\u000firectives.html>\r\n# for a \u001b[30m\u001b[103md\u001b[m\u000fiscussion of each configuration \u001b[30m\u001b[103md\u001b[m\u000firective.\u001b[8;2H\u001b[27X\n Do \u001b[0;10;1m\u000fNOT\u001b[m\u000f simply rea\u001b[30m\u001b[103md\u001b[m\u000f the instructions in here without un\u001b[30m\u001b[103md\u001b[m\u000ferstan\u001b[30m\u001b[103md\u001b[m\u000fing\u001b[10;3Hwhat they \u001b[30m\u001b[103md\u001b[m\u000fo.  They're here only as hints or remin\u001b[30m\u001b[103md\u001b[m\u000fers.  If you are unsure\u001b[11;3Hconsult the online \u001b[30m\u001b[103md\u001b[m\u000focs. You have been warne\u001b[30m\u001b[103md\u001b[m\u000f.  \u001b[25X\u001b[12;2H\u001b[70X\u001b[13;3HConfiguration an\u001b[30m\u001b[103md\u001b[m\u000f logfile names: If the filenames you specify for many\r\n# of the server's control files begin with \"/\" (or \"\u001b[30m\u001b[103md\u001b[m\u000frive:/\" for Win32), the\u001b[15;3Hserver will use that explicit path.  If the filenames \u001b[30m\u001b[103md\u001b[m\u000fo *not* begin\r\n# with \"/\", the value of ServerRoot is prepen\u001b[30m\u001b[103md\u001b[m\u000fe\u001b[30m\u001b[103md\u001b[m\u000f -- so \"logs/access_log\"\r\n# with ServerRoot set to \"/usr/local/apache2\" will be interprete\u001b[30m\u001b[103md\u001b[m\u000f by the\u001b[18;3Hserver as \"/usr/local/apache2/logs/access_log\", whereas \"/logs/access_log\" \r\n# will be interprete\u001b[30m\u001b[103md\u001b[m\u000f as '/logs/access_log'.    \u001b[21;2H\u001b[25X\r\n# ServerRoot: The top of the \u001b[30m\u001b[103md\u001b[m\u000firectory tree un\u001b[30m\u001b[103md\u001b[m\u000fer which the server's\r\n# configuration, error, an\u001b[30m\u001b[103md\u001b[m\u000f log files are kept.\u001b[24;2H\u001b[18X\r\n# Do not a\u001b[30m\u001b[103mdd\u001b[m\u000f a slash at the en\u001b[30m\u001b[103md\u001b[m\u000f of the \u001b[30m\u001b[103md\u001b[m\u000firectory path.  If you point\r\n# ServerRoot at a non-local \u001b[30m\u001b[103md\u001b[m\u000fisk, be sure to specify a local \u001b[30m\u001b[103md\u001b[m\u000fisk on the\u001b[27;3HMutex \u001b[30m\u001b[103md\u001b[m\u000firective, if file-base\u001b[30m\u001b[103md\u001b[m\u000f mutexes are use\u001b[30m\u001b[103md\u001b[m\u000f.  If you wish to share the\r\n# same ServerRoot for multiple http\u001b[30m\u001b[103md\u001b[m\u000f \u001b[30m\u001b[103md\u001b[m\u000faemons, you will nee\u001b[30m\u001b[103md\u001b[m\u000f to change at\r\n# least Pi\u001b[30m\u001b[103md\u001b[m\u000fFile.\u001b[30;2H\u001b[45X\r\n\u001b[96mServerRoot\u001b[m\u000f \u001b[92m\"/etc/http\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[30m\u001b[103md\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[92m\"\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[12X\u001b[33;2H\u001b[14X\n Mutex: Allows you to set the mutex mechanism an\u001b[30m\u001b[103md\u001b[m\u000f mutex file \u001b[30m\u001b[103md\u001b[m\u000firectory\r\n# for in\u001b[30m\u001b[103md\u001b[m\u000fivi\u001b[30m\u001b[103md\u001b[m\u000fual mutexes, or change the global \u001b[30m\u001b[103md\u001b[m\u000fefaults\u001b[36;2H\u001b[46X\n Uncomment an\u001b[30m\u001b[103md\u001b[m\u000f change the \u001b[30m\u001b[103md\u001b[m\u000firectory if mutexes are file-base\u001b[30m\u001b[103md\u001b[m\u000f an\u001b[30m\u001b[103md\u001b[m\u000f the \u001b[30m\u001b[103md\u001b[m\u000fefault\r\n# mutex file \u001b[30m\u001b[103md\u001b[m\u000firectory is not on a local \u001b[30m\u001b[103md\u001b[m\u000fisk or is not appropriate for some\u001b[39;3Hother reason.\u001b[32X\u001b[40;2H\u001b[33X\r\n# Mutex \u001b[30m\u001b[103md\u001b[m\u000fefault:/run/http\u001b[30m\u001b[103md\u001b[m\u000f\r\n\u001b[26X\n#\u001b[36X\r\n# Listen: Allows you to bin\u001b[30m\u001b[103md\u001b[m\u000f Apache to specific IP a\u001b[30m\u001b[103mdd\u001b[m\u000fresses an\u001b[30m\u001b[103md\u001b[m\u000f/or\u001b[45;3Hports, instea\u001b[30m\u001b[103md\u001b[m\u000f of the \u001b[30m\u001b[103md\u001b[m\u000fefault. See also the <VirtualHost>\r\n# \u001b[30m\u001b[103md\u001b[m\u000firective.\u001b[16X\r\n#\u001b[33X\r\n# Change this to Listen on specific IP a\u001b[30m\u001b[103mdd\u001b[m\u000fresses as shown below to \r\n# prevent Apache from glomming onto all boun\u001b[30m\u001b[103md\u001b[m\u000f IP a\u001b[30m\u001b[103mdd\u001b[m\u000fresses.\u001b[50;2H\u001b[29X\nListen 12.34.56.78:80\u001b[12X\r\n\u001b[96mListen\u001b[m\u000f 80\r\n\u001b[48X\u001b[54;2H\u001b[71X\u001b[55;3HDynamic Share\u001b[30m\u001b[103md\u001b[m\u000f Object (DSO) Support\u001b[8X\r\n\n# To be able to use the functionality of a mo\u001b[30m\u001b[103md\u001b[m\u000fule which was built as a DSO you\r\n# have to place correspon\u001b[30m\u001b[103md\u001b[m\u000fing `Loa\u001b[30m\u001b[103md\u001b[m\u000fMo\u001b[30m\u001b[103md\u001b[m\u000fule' lines at this location so the\r\n# \u001b[30m\u001b[103md\u001b[m\u000firectives containe\u001b[30m\u001b[103md\u001b[m\u000f in it are actually available _before_ they are use\u001b[30m\u001b[103md\u001b[m\u000f.\r\n# Statically compile\u001b[30m\u001b[103md\u001b[m\u000f mo\u001b[30m\u001b[103md\u001b[m\u000fules (those liste\u001b[30m\u001b[103md\u001b[m\u000f by `http\u001b[30m\u001b[103md\u001b[m\u000f -l') \u001b[30m\u001b[103md\u001b[m\u000fo not nee\u001b[30m\u001b[103md\r\n\u001b[m\u000f# to be loa\u001b[30m\u001b[103md\u001b[m\u000fe\u001b[30m\u001b[103md\u001b[m\u000f here.\r\n#\u001b[33X\r\n# Example:\u001b[11X\r\n# Loa\u001b[30m\u001b[103md\u001b[m\u000fMo\u001b[30m\u001b[103md\u001b[m\u000fule foo_mo\u001b[30m\u001b[103md\u001b[m\u000fule mo\u001b[30m\u001b[1"]
