[0.010, "o", "\u001b[3;18H\u001b[30m\u001b[103mi\u001b[4;23H\u001b[m\u000fd.apache.org/docs/2.4/> for detailed\u001b[6;19Hd.apache.org/docs/2.4/mod/\u001b[30m\u001b[103mdi\u001b[7;10Hi\u001b[m\u000fscussion of each configuration \u001b[30m\u001b[103mdi\u001b[9;20H\u001b[m\u000fd the instructions in here without understan\u001b[30m\u001b[103mdi\u001b[10;13H\u001b[m\u000fdo.  They're here only as hints or remind\u001b[11;22Hdocs. You have been warned\u001b[13;19Hd\u001b[14;53Hd\u001b[15;57Hd\u001b[16;46Hded\u001b[17;65Hd\u001b[19;21Hd\u001b[22;31H\u001b[30m\u001b[103mi\u001b[m\u000frectory tree und\u001b[23;27Hd\u001b[25;11Hdd a slash at the end of the \u001b[30m\u001b[103mdi\u001b[26;30Hi\u001b[m\u000fsk, be sure to specify a local \u001b[30m\u001b[103mdi\u001b[27;10Hi\u001b[m\u000frective, if file-based mutexes are used\u001b[28;36Hd daemons, you will need\u001b[29;11Hd\u001b[31;22H\u001b[92md\u001b[34;50H\u001b[m\u000fd mutex file \u001b[30m\u001b[103mdi\u001b[35;10Hi\u001b[m\u000fvidual mutexes, or change the global d\u001b[37;15Hd change the \u001b[30m\u001b[103mdi\u001b[m\u000frectory if mutexes are file-based and the d\u001b[38;15H\u001b[30m\u001b[103mi\u001b[m\u000frectory is not on a local \u001b[30m\u001b[103mdi\u001b[41;9H\u001b[m\u000fdefault:/run/httpd\u001b[44;28Hd Apache to specific IP addresses and\u001b[45;16Hd of the d\u001b[46;4H\u001b[30m\u001b[103mi\u001b[48;41H\u001b[m\u000fdd\u001b[49;45Hd IP add\u001b[55;16Hd\u001b[57;46Hd\u001b[58;27H\u001b[30m\u001b[103mi\u001b[m\u000fng `LoadMod\u001b[59;4H\u001b[30m\u001b[103mi\u001b[m\u000frectives contained in it are actually available _before_ they are used\u001b[60;21Hd modules (those listed by `httpd -l') do not need\u001b[61;12Hded\u001b[64;6HdModule foo_module modules/mod\u001b[67;4H\u001b[?25h"]
