[0.005, "o", "\u001b[6;27He, generally called php.ini, is responsible\u001b[7;25He aspects of PHP's be\u001b[9;10Hempts to find and load this configuration from a numbe\u001b[10;5He following is a summary of its search orde\u001b[11;16He spe\u001b[12;8He PHPRC environment variable\u001b[13;12Her of predefined registry ke\u001b[14;10Hent working directory (\u001b[30m\u001b[103mex\u001b[m\u000fce\u001b[15;8He web server's directory (for SAPI modules), or dire\u001b[16;7Herwise\u001b[17;8He directory from the --with-config-file-path compile time option, or the\u001b[18;14He\u001b[19;4Hee the PHP docs for more spe\u001b[20;16Het/configuration.file\u001b[22;5He syntax of the file is \u001b[30m\u001b[103mex\u001b[m\u000ftremely simple.  Whitespace and line\u001b[23;4Heginning with a semicolon are silently ignored (as you probably guesse\u001b[24;4Hection headers (e.g. [Foo]) are also silently ignored, eve\u001b[25;5Hey might mean something in the future\u001b[27;6Hectives following the section heading [PATH=/www/mysite\u001b[28;19Hes in the /www/mysite directory.  Directive\u001b[29;15He section heading [HOST=www.\u001b[30m\u001b[103mex\u001b[m\u000fample\u001b[30;10Hes served from www.\u001b[30m\u001b[103mex\u001b[m\u000fample.com.  Directives set in these\u001b[31;5Hecial sections cannot be overridden by user-defined INI file\u001b[32;12He. Currently, [PATH=] and [HOST=] sections only work unde\u001b[34;16Het/ini.se\u001b[36;6Hectives are specified using the\u001b[37;6Hective = value\u001b[38;6Hective names are *case sensitive* - foo=bar is differe\u001b[39;6Hectives are variables used to configure PHP or PHP \u001b[30m\u001b[103mex\u001b[m\u000fte\u001b[40;5Here is no name validation.  If PHP can't find an \u001b[30m\u001b[103mex\u001b[m\u000fpecte\u001b[41;6Hective because it is not set or is mistyped, a default value will be use\u001b[43;5He value can be a string, a number, a PHP constant (e.g. E_ALL or M_PI), one\u001b[44;8He INI constants (On, Off, True, False, Yes, No and None) or an \u001b[30m\u001b[103mex\u001b[m\u000fpre\u001b[45;4He.g. E_ALL & ~E_NOTICE), a quoted string (\"bar\"), or a reference\u001b[46;5Heviously set variable or directive (e\u001b[48;7Hessions in the INI file are limited to bitwise operators and parenthese\u001b[49;12He\u001b[50;12He\u001b[51;12He\u001b[52;12He\u001b[53;10He\u001b[55;7Hean flags can be turned on using the values 1, On, True or Ye\u001b[56;5Hey can be turned off using the values 0, Off, False\u001b[58;6Hempty string can be denoted by simply not writing anything after the e\u001b[59;23He None ke\u001b[61;20Hets foo to an e\u001b[62;12He    ; sets foo to an e\u001b[63;13He\"  ; sets foo to the string 'None\u001b[65;12He constants in your value, and these constants be\u001b[66;223H\u001b[0;10;7m\u000f14,33\u001b[67;4H\u001b[?25h"]
