[0.005, "o", "\u001b[H;highlight.string  = #DD0000\u001b[2;2Hhighlight.comment = #FF9900\u001b[3;2Hhighlight.keyword = #007700\u001b[4;2Hhighlight.default = #0000BB\u001b[5;2Hhighlight.html    = #000000\u001b[45X\r\n\u001b[52X\n; If enabled, the request will be allowed to complete even if the user aborts\u001b[8;3Hthe request. Consider enabling it if executing long requests, which may end up\u001b[9;3Hbeing interrupted by the user or a browser timing out. PHP's default behavior\u001b[10;3His to disable this feature.\u001b[6X\u001b[11;3Hhttps://php.net/ignore-user-abort \u001b[12;2Hignore_user_abort = On\u001b[29X\r\n\u001b[43X\u001b[14;3HDetermines the size of the realpath cache to be used by PHP. This value should\u001b[15;3Hbe increased on systems where PHP opens many files to reflect the quantity of\u001b[16;3Hthe file operations performed.\u001b[47X\u001b[17;3HNote: if open_basedir is set, the cache is disabled\u001b[18;3Hhttps://php.net/realpath-cache-size\u001b[12X\u001b[19;2Hrealpath_cache_size = 4096k\u001b[8X\u001b[21;3HDuration of time, in seconds for which to cache realpath information for a given\u001b[22;3Hfile or directory. For systems with rarely changing files, consider increasing this\u001b[23;3Hvalue.\u001b[61X\u001b[24;3Hhttps://php.net/realpath-cache-ttl\u001b[6X\r\n;realpath_cache_ttl = 120\r\n\u001b[66X\u001b[27;3HEnables or disables the circular reference collector.\u001b[7X\u001b[28;3Hhttps://php.net/zend.enable-gc\u001b[36X\r\nzend.enable_gc =\u001b[92m On\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[46X\r\n\u001b[68X\u001b[31;3HIf enabled, scripts may be written in encodings that are incompatible with\u001b[32;3Hthe scanner.  CP936, Big5, CP949 and Shift_JIS are the examples of such\u001b[33;3Hencodings.  To use this feature, mbstring \u001b[30m\u001b[103mextension m\u001b[m\u000fust be enabled.\r\n;zend.multibyte = Off\r\n\u001b[54X\u001b[36;3HAllows to set the default encoding for the scripts.  This value will be used\u001b[37;3Hunless \"declare(encoding=...)\" directive appears at the top of the script.\u001b[38;3HOnly affects if zend.multibyte is set.\u001b[27X\u001b[39;2Hzend.script_encoding =\u001b[38X\r\n\u001b[79X\n; Allows to include or exclude arguments from stack traces generated for exceptions.\u001b[42;3HIn production, it is recommended to turn this setting on to prohibit the output\u001b[43;6Hsensitive information in stack traces\u001b[38X\u001b[44;3HDefault Value: Off\u001b[52X\u001b[45;3HDevelopment Value: Off\u001b[28X\r\n; Production Value: On\r\nzend.exception_ignore_args =\u001b[92m On\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[48X\r\n\u001b[15X\u001b[49;3HAllows setting the maximum string length in an argument of a stringified stack trace\u001b[50;3Hto a value between 0 and 1000000.\u001b[51;3HThis has no effect when zend.exception_ignore_args is enabled.\u001b[52;3HDefault Value: 15\r\n; Development Value: 15\u001b[54;3HProduction Value: 0\u001b[48X\u001b[55;3HIn production, it is recommended to set this to 0 to reduce the output\r\n; of sensitive information in stack traces.\r\nzend.exception_string_param_max_len = 0\u001b[40X\r\n\u001b[37X\n;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;\u001b[60;3HMiscellaneous ;\u001b[28X\u001b[61;2H;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;\u001b[28X\r\n\u001b[47X\n; Decides whether PHP may expose the fact that it is installed on the server\u001b[64;3H(e.g. by adding its signature to the Web server header).  It is no security\u001b[65;3Hthreat in any way, but it makes it possible to determine whether you use PHP\u001b[66;223H\u001b[0;10;7m\u000f360,45         18\u001b[67;13H\u001b[?25h"]
[3.660, "o", "\u001b[?25l\b\u001b[m\u000f \b"]
[0.005, "o", "\u001b[H\u001b[28X\u001b[2;2H;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;\u001b[9X\u001b[3;2H About php.ini   ;\u001b[9X\u001b[4;2H;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;\u001b[9X\u001b[5;2H PHP's initialization file, generally called php.ini, is responsible for\r\n; configuring many of the aspects of PHP's behavior.\r\n\u001b[77X\u001b[8;3HPHP attempts to find and load this configuration from a number of locations.  \u001b[9;3HThe following is a summary of its search order:\u001b[30X\u001b[10;3H1. SAPI module specific location.\u001b[11;3H2. The PHPRC environment variable.\u001b[12;2H 3. A number of predefined registry keys on Windows\r\n; 4. Current working directory (except CLI)\u001b[14;3H5. The web server's directory (for SAPI modules), or directory of PHP\u001b[9X\u001b[15;3H(otherwise in Windows)\u001b[55X\u001b[16;3H6. The directory from the --with-config-file-path compile time option, or the\u001b[17;3HWindows directory (usually C:\\windows)\u001b[13X\u001b[18;3HSee the PHP docs for more specific information.\u001b[19;2H https://php.net/configuration.file\u001b[21;3HThe syntax of the file is extremely simple.  Whitespace and lines\u001b[15X\u001b[22;3Hbeginning with a semicolon are silently ignored (as you probably guessed).\u001b[9X\u001b[23;3HSection headers (e.g. [Foo]) are also silently ignored, even though\u001b[24;3Hthey might mean something in the future.\r\n\u001b[25X\n; Directives following the section heading [PATH=/www/mysite] only\u001b[27;3Happly to PHP files in the /www/mysite directory.  Directives\u001b[28;3Hfollowing the section heading [HOST=www.example.com] only apply to\r\n; PHP files served from www.example.com.  Directives set in these\r\n; special sections cannot be overridden by user-defined INI files or\u001b[31;3Hat runtime. Currently, [PATH=] and [HOST=] sections only work under\u001b[7X\u001b[32;3HCGI/FastCGI.\u001b[59X\u001b[33;3Hhttps://php.net/ini.sections\u001b[40X\r\n\u001b[21X\n; Directives are specified using the following syntax:\u001b[36;3Hdirective = value\u001b[59X\u001b[37;3HDirective names are *case sensitive* - foo=bar is different from FOO=bar. \u001b[38;3HDirectives are variables used to configure PHP or PHP extensions.\u001b[39;2H There is no name validation.  If PHP can't find an expected\r\n; directive because it is not set or is mistyped, a default value will be used.\r\n\u001b[84X\u001b[42;3HThe value can be a string, a number, a PHP constant (e.g. E_ALL or M_PI), one  \u001b[43;6Hthe INI constants (On, Off, True, False, Yes, No and None) or an expression\u001b[44;3H(e.g. E_ALL & ~E_NOTICE), a quoted string (\"bar\"), or a reference to a\u001b[45;3Hpreviously set variable or directive (e.g. ${foo})\r\n\u001b[22X\n; Expressions in the INI file are limited to bitwise operators and parentheses:\r\n; |  bitwise OR\u001b[49;3H^  bitwise XOR\u001b[70X\u001b[50;3H&  bitwise AND\u001b[19X\u001b[51;3H~  bitwise NOT\u001b[48X\u001b[52;3H!  boolean NOT   \r\n\u001b[23X\u001b[54;3HBoolean flags can be turned on using the values 1, On, True or Yes.\u001b[55;3HThey can be turned off using the values 0, Off, False or No.\u001b[10X\r\n\u001b[43X\n; An empty string can be denoted by simply not writing anything after the equal\r\n; sign, or by using the None keyword:\r\n\u001b[17X\u001b[60;3Hfoo =         ; sets foo to an empty string\u001b[61;2H foo = None    ; sets foo to an empty string\r\n; foo = \"None\"  ; sets foo to the string 'None'\r\n\u001b[76X\u001b[64;3HIf you use constants in your value, and these constants belong to a\u001b[8X\u001b[65;3Hdynamically loaded \u001b[30m\u001b[103mextension \u001b[m\u000f(either a PHP \u001b[30m\u001b[103mextension \u001b[m\u000for a Zend extension),  \u001b[66;223H\u001b[0;10;7m\u000f66,22           0\u001b[67;12H\u001b[?25h"]
[0.608, "o", "\u001b[?25l\b"]
[0.005, "o", "\u001b[1;65r\u001b[H\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[L\u001b[1;67r\u001b[H\u001b[96m[PHP]\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[K\u001b[39;57H\u001b[30m\u001b[103mextension\u001b[66;223H\u001b[0;10;7m\u000f39,57          Top\u001b[67;11H\u001b[?25h"]
[0.874, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[m\u000f="]
[0.004, "o", "\u001b[H; Whether to allow include/require to open URLs (like https:// or ftp://) as files.\r\n; https://php.net/allow-url-include\r\nallow_url_include =\u001b[92m Off\u001b[m\u000f\r\n\u001b[19X\u001b[5;2H Define the anonymous ftp password (your email address). PHP's default setting\u001b[6;3Hfor this is empty.\u001b[53X\u001b[7;3Hhttps://php.net/from\u001b[30X\r\n;from=\"john@doe.com\"\r\n\u001b[78X\u001b[10;3HDefine the User-Agent string. PHP's default setting for this is empty.\u001b[11;3Hhttps://php.net/user-agent\u001b[7X\u001b[12;2Huser_agent=\"PHP\"\u001b[19X\r\n\u001b[52X\u001b[14;3HDefault timeout for socket based streams (seconds)\u001b[15;3Hhttps://php.net/default-socket-timeout\u001b[31X\r\ndefault_socket_timeout = 60\r\n\u001b[79X\u001b[18;3HIf your scripts have to deal with files from Macintosh systems,\u001b[19;3Hor you are running on a Mac and need to deal with files from\u001b[20;3Hunix or win32 systems, setting this flag will cause PHP to\r\n; automatically detect the EOL character in those files so that\u001b[22;3Hfgets() and file() will work regardless of the source of the file.\u001b[23;3Hhttps://php.net/auto-detect-line-endings\u001b[34X\u001b[24;2Hauto_detect_line_endings = Off\u001b[38X\r\n\u001b[42X\n;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;\u001b[27;4Hynamic Extensions ;\u001b[44X\u001b[28;2H;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;\u001b[40X\r\n\u001b[68X\u001b[30;3HIf you wish to have an extension loaded automatically, use the following\u001b[31;4Hyntax:\u001b[59X\u001b[32;2H\u001b[68X\u001b[33;3H  \u001b[30m\u001b[103mextension=\u001b[m\u000fmodulename\u001b[34;2H\u001b[29X\r\n; For example:\u001b[36;2H\u001b[53X\u001b[37;3H  \u001b[30m\u001b[103mextension=\u001b[m\u000fmysqli\u001b[38;2H\u001b[74X\u001b[39;3HWhen the extension library to load is not located in the default extension\u001b[40;3Hdirectory, You may specify an absolute path to the library file:\u001b[41;2H\u001b[78X\r\n;   \u001b[30m\u001b[103mextension=\u001b[m\u000f/path/to/extension/mysqli.so\u001b[43;2H\u001b[78X\u001b[44;3HNote : The syntax used in previous PHP versions ('\u001b[30m\u001b[103mextension=\u001b[m\u000f<ext>.so' and\u001b[5X\u001b[45;3H'\u001b[30m\u001b[103mextension=\u001b[m\u000f'php_<ext>.dll') is supported for legacy reasons and may be\u001b[46;3Hdeprecated in a future PHP major version. So, when it is possible, please\r\n; move to the new ('\u001b[30m\u001b[103mextension=\u001b[m\u000f<ext>) syntax.\u001b[48;2H\u001b[78X\n\u001b[30m\u001b[103mextension=\u001b[m\u000fbcmath\u001b[50;2H\u001b[30m\u001b[103mextension=\u001b[m\u000fbz2  \u001b[51;2H\u001b[30m\u001b[103mextension=\u001b[m\u000fcalendar\r\n\u001b[30m\u001b[103mextension=\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[92mcurl\u001b[m\u000f  \u001b[53;2H\u001b[30m\u001b[103mextension=\u001b[m\u000fdba  \r\n;\u001b[30m\u001b[103mextension=\u001b[m\u000fenchant\u001b[55;2H\u001b[30m\u001b[103mextension=\u001b[m\u000fexif\u001b[54X\u001b[56;2H\u001b[30m\u001b[103mextension=\u001b[m\u000fffi\u001b[48X\r\n;\u001b[30m\u001b[103mextension=\u001b[m\u000fftp\u001b[58;2H\u001b[30m\u001b[103mextension=\u001b[m\u000fgd\u001b[66X\u001b[59;2H\u001b[30m\u001b[103mextension=\u001b[m\u000fgettext\u001b[19X\r\n;\u001b[30m\u001b[103mextension=\u001b[m\u000fgmp\u001b[61;2H\u001b[30m\u001b[103mextension=\u001b[m\u000ficonv\u001b[29X\u001b[62;2H\u001b[30m\u001b[103mextension=\u001b[m\u000fintl\u001b[30X\u001b[63;2H\u001b[30m\u001b[103mextension=\u001b[m\u000fldap\u001b[32X\r\n;\u001b[30m\u001b[103mextension=\u001b[m\u000fmysqli\u001b[65;2H\u001b[30m\u001b[103mextension=\u001b[m\u000fodbc\u001b[54X\u001b[66;223H\u001b[0;10;7m\u000f896,5          47%\u001b[67;12H\u001b[?25h"]
