[0.003, "o", "\u001b[1;79H\u001b[30m\u001b[103mg\u001b[6;20Hg\u001b[m\u000fent strin\u001b[30m\u001b[103mg\u001b[m\u000f. PHP's default settin\u001b[30m\u001b[103mg\u001b[7;25Hg\u001b[8;8Hg\u001b[15;20Hg\u001b[16;32Hg\u001b[m\u000f this fla\u001b[30m\u001b[103mg\u001b[18;4Hg\u001b[m\u000fets() and file() will work re\u001b[30m\u001b[103mg\u001b[19;41Hg\u001b[20;24Hg\u001b[26;74Hg\u001b[41;50Hg\u001b[54;12Hg\u001b[55;11Hg\ng\u001b[63;11H\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[92mpdo_mysql\u001b[65;17H\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[30m\u001b[103mg\u001b[66;225H\u001b[0;10;7m\u000f2,17\u001b[67;3H\u001b[?25h"]
[0.210, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[m\u000fd"]
[0.005, "o", "\u001b[1;3Hconverted to internal encoding by setting this to On.\u001b[24X\u001b[2;3HNote: Do _not_ use automatic encoding translation for\u001b[3;3H      portable libs/applications.\u001b[4;2H https://php.net/mbstring.encoding-translation\r\n;mbstring.encoding_translation = Off\r\n\u001b[72X\u001b[7;3Hautomatic encoding detection order.\u001b[8;2H \"auto\" detect order is changed according to mbstring.language\r\n; https://php.net/mbstring.detect-order\u001b[10;2Hmbstring.detect_order = auto\u001b[23X\r\n\u001b[40X\n; substitute_character used when character cannot be converted\r\n; one from another\u001b[14;3Hhttps://php.net/mbstring.substitute-character\u001b[18X\u001b[15;2Hmbstring.substitute_character = none\u001b[25X\r\n\u001b[60X\u001b[17;3HEnable strict encoding detection.\u001b[28X\u001b[18;2Hmbstring.strict_detection = Off\u001b[36X\r\n\u001b[42X\u001b[20;2H This directive specifies the regex pattern of content types for which mb_output_handler()\r\n; is activated.\u001b[22;2H Default: mbstring.http_output_conv_mimetypes=^(text/|application/xhtml\\+xml)\u001b[23;2Hmbstring.http_output_conv_mimetypes=\r\n\u001b[22X\n; This directive specifies maximum stack depth for mbstring regular expressions. It is similar\u001b[26;3Hto the pcre.recursion_limit for PCRE.\u001b[35X\u001b[27;2Hmbstring.regex_stack_limit=100000\r\n \u001b[29;3HThis directive specifies maximum retry count for mbstring regular expressions. It is similar\u001b[30;2H to the pcre.backtrack_limit for PCRE.\u001b[31;2Hmbstring.regex_retry_limit=1000000\r\n \r\n\u001b[96m[\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[30m\u001b[103mgd\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[96m]\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[16X\u001b[34;2H Tell the jpeg decode to ignore warnings and try to create\u001b[35;3Ha \u001b[30m\u001b[103mgd\u001b[m\u000f image. The warning will then be displayed as notices\u001b[17X\u001b[36;5Hsabled by default\u001b[45X\u001b[37;2H https://php.net/\u001b[30m\u001b[103mgd\u001b[m\u000f.jpeg-ignore-warning\u001b[38;2H\u001b[30m\u001b[103mgd\u001b[m\u000f.jpeg_ignore_warning = 1\u001b[15X\r\n \r\n\u001b[96m[exif]\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[69X\u001b[41;3HExif UNICODE user comments are handled as UCS-2BE/UCS-2LE and JIS as JIS.\u001b[42;3HWith mbstring support this will automatically be converted into the encoding\u001b[43;3Hgiven by corresponding encode setting. When empty mbstring.internal_encoding\u001b[44;2H is used. For the decode settings you can distinguish between motorola and\u001b[45;2H intel byte order. A decode setting must not be empty.\u001b[46;2H https://php.net/exif.encode-unicode\u001b[47;4Hif.encode_unicode = ISO-8859-15\r\n\u001b[14X\u001b[49;2H https://php.net/exif.decode-unicode-motorola\u001b[50;4Hif.decode_unicode_motorola = UCS-2BE\r\n\u001b[15X\u001b[52;2H https://php.net/exif.decode-unicode-intel\u001b[53;4Hif.decode_unicode_intel    = UCS-2LE\r\n\u001b[13X\n; https://php.net/exif.encode-jis\u001b[56;4Hif.encode_jis =\r\n\u001b[16X\u001b[58;2H https://php.net/exif.decode-jis-motorola\u001b[59;4Hif.decode_jis_motorola = JIS\r\n\u001b[16X\u001b[61;2H https://php.net/exif.decode-jis-intel\u001b[62;4Hif.decode_jis_intel    = JIS\r\n\u001b[19X\n\u001b[96m[Tidy]\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[13X\u001b[65;2H The path to a default tidy configuration file to use when using tidy\u001b[66;223H\u001b[0;10;7m\u000f1602,2         86\u001b[67;4H\u001b[?25h"]
[4.234, "o", "\u001b[?25l\b\u001b[m\u000f \b"]
[0.004, "o", "\u001b[66ADefine the anonymous ftp password (your email address). PHP's default settin\u001b[30m\u001b[103mg\u001b[2;3H\u001b[m\u000ffor this is empty.\u001b[35X\u001b[3;3Hhttps://php.net/from\u001b[13X\u001b[4;2Hfrom=\"john@doe.com\"\u001b[27X\r\n\u001b[36X\n; Define the User-A\u001b[30m\u001b[103mg\u001b[m\u000fent strin\u001b[30m\u001b[103mg\u001b[m\u000f. PHP's default settin\u001b[30m\u001b[103mg\u001b[m\u000f for this is empty.\u001b[7;3Hhttps://php.net/user-a\u001b[30m\u001b[103mg\u001b[m\u000fent\u001b[9X\u001b[8;2Huser_a\u001b[30m\u001b[103mg\u001b[m\u000fent=\"PHP\"\u001b[46X\r\n\u001b[39X\u001b[10;2H Default timeout for socket based streams (seconds)\r\n; https://php.net/default-socket-timeout\r\ndefault_socket_timeout = 60\u001b[35X\r\n\u001b[18X\u001b[14;3HIf your scripts have to deal with files from Macintosh systems,\u001b[15;2H or you are runnin\u001b[30m\u001b[103mg\u001b[m\u000f on a Mac and need to deal with files from\r\n; unix or win32 systems, settin\u001b[30m\u001b[103mg\u001b[m\u000f this fla\u001b[30m\u001b[103mg\u001b[m\u000f will cause PHP to\u001b[17;3Hautomatically detect the EOL character in those files so that\u001b[18;2H f\u001b[30m\u001b[103mg\u001b[m\u000fets() and file() will work re\u001b[30m\u001b[103mg\u001b[m\u000fardless of the source of the file.\r\n; https://php.net/auto-detect-line-endin\u001b[30m\u001b[103mg\u001b[m\u000fs\u001b[20;2Hauto_detect_line_endin\u001b[30m\u001b[103mg\u001b[m\u000fs = Off\u001b[60X\r\n\u001b[15X\u001b[22;2H;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;\u001b[56X\u001b[23;2H Dynamic Extensions ;\u001b[15X\r\n;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;\r\n\u001b[94X\u001b[26;3HIf you wish to have an extension loaded automatically, use the followin\u001b[30m\u001b[103mg\u001b[27;2H\u001b[m\u000f syntax:\u001b[25X\r\n;\u001b[29;3H  extension=modulename\u001b[70X\u001b[30;2H\u001b[38X\n For example:\u001b[21X\r\n;\r\n;   extension=mysqli\u001b[34;2H\u001b[58X\u001b[35;3HWhen the extension library to load is not located in the default extension\u001b[36;5Hrectory, You may specify an absolute path to the library file:\u001b[37;2H\u001b[39X\n   extension=/path/to/extension/mysqli.so\r\n;\r\n; Note : The syntax used in previous PHP versions ('extension=<ext>.so' and\u001b[41;3H'extension='php_<ext>.dll') is supported for le\u001b[30m\u001b[103mg\u001b[m\u000facy reasons and may be   \u001b[42;3Hdeprecated in a future PHP major version. So, when it is possible, please   \u001b[43;3Hmove to the new ('extension=<ext>) syntax.\u001b[34X\u001b[44;2H\u001b[74X\nextension=bcmath\u001b[38X\u001b[46;2Hextension=bz2\u001b[23X\u001b[47;4Htension=calendar\u001b[15X\r\nextension=\u001b[92mcurl\u001b[49;2H\u001b[m\u000fextension=dba\u001b[32X\u001b[50;4Htension=enchant\u001b[21X\r\n;extension=exif\u001b[52;2Hextension=ffi\u001b[29X\u001b[53;4Htension=ftp\u001b[25X\r\n;extension=\u001b[30m\u001b[103mg\u001b[m\u000fd\r\nextension=\u001b[30m\u001b[103mg\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[92mettext\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[16X\u001b[56;4Htension=\u001b[30m\u001b[103mg\u001b[m\u000fmp    \r\n;extension=iconv\u001b[58;2Hextension=intl\u001b[27X\u001b[59;4Htension=ldap\u001b[16X\r\nextension=\u001b[92mmysqli\u001b[61;2H\u001b[m\u000fextension=odbc\u001b[24X\u001b[62;4Htension=pdo_dblib\u001b[11X\r\nextension=\u001b[92mpdo_mysql\r\n\u001b[m\u000f;extension=pdo_odbc\u001b[65;2Hextension=pdo_p\u001b[30m\u001b[103mg\u001b[m\u000fsql\u001b[50X\u001b[66;223H\u001b[0;10;7m\u000f932,17         47\u001b[67;3H\u001b[?25h"]
