[0.026, "o", "\u001b[?25l\b\u001b[m\u000f \b"]
[0.005, "o", "\u001b[1;2H;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;  \r\n\u001b[22X\n; Enable the PHP scripting language engine under Apache.\u001b[4;3Hhttps://php.net/engine\u001b[50X\r\nengine =\u001b[92m On\r\n\u001b[m\u000f \u001b[7;3HThis directive determines whether or not PHP will recognize code between\u001b[8;2H <? and ?> tags as PHP source which should be processed as such. It is\u001b[9;3Hgenerally recommended that <?php and ?> should be used and that this feature\u001b[10;2H should be disabled, as enabling it may result in issues when generating XML\u001b[11;3Hdocuments, however this remains supported for backward compatibility reasons.\u001b[12;2H Note that this directive does not control the <?= shorthand tag, which can be\u001b[13;3Hused regardless of this directive.\u001b[40X\u001b[14;3HDefault Value: On\u001b[47X\u001b[15;2H Development Value: Off\u001b[16;3HProduction Value: Off\u001b[19X\u001b[17;2H https://php.net/short-open-tag\r\nshort_open_tag =\u001b[92m Off\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[55X\r\n\u001b[72X\u001b[20;3HThe number of significant digits displayed in floating point numbers.    \u001b[21;3Hhttps://php.net/precision\u001b[17X\r\nprecision = 14\r\n\u001b[17X\u001b[24;2H Output buffering is a mechanism for controlling how much output data\u001b[25;2H (excluding headers and cookies) PHP should keep internally before pushing that\r\n; data to the client. If your application's output exceeds this setting, PHP\u001b[27;2H will send that data in chunks of roughly the size you specify.\u001b[28;2H Turning on this setting and managing its maximum buffer size can yield some\u001b[29;2H interesting side-effects depending on your application and web server.\u001b[30;2H You may be able to send headers and cookies after you've already sent output\u001b[31;2H through print or echo. You also may see performance benefits if your server is\r\n; emitting less packets due to buffered output versus PHP streaming the output\r\n; as it \u001b[30m\u001b[103mget\u001b[m\u000fs it. On production servers, 4096 bytes is a good setting for performance\u001b[34;2H reasons.    \u001b[35;2H Note: Output buffering can also be controlled via Output Buffering Control\u001b[36;2H   functions. \u001b[37;2H Possible Values:\r\n;   On = Enabled and buffer is unlimited. (Use with caution)\u001b[39;2H   Off = Disabled\u001b[40;2H   Integer = Enables the buffer and sets its maximum size in bytes.\r\n; Note: This directive is hardcoded to Off for the CLI SAPI\u001b[42;2H Default Value: Off\u001b[43;2H Development Value: 4096\u001b[44;2H Production Value: 4096\u001b[45;2H https://php.net/output-buffering\r\noutput_buffering = 4096\r\n\u001b[15X\u001b[48;2H You can redirect all of the output of your scripts to a function.  For\u001b[49;2H example, if you set output_handler to \"mb_output_handler\", character\u001b[50;2H encoding will be transparently converted to the specified encoding.\u001b[51;2H Setting any output handler automatically turns on output buffering.\u001b[52;2H Note: People who wrote portable scripts should not depend on this ini\u001b[53;2H   directive. Instead, explicitly set the output handler using ob_start().\u001b[54;2H   Using this ini directive may cause problems unless you know what script\u001b[55;2H   is doing.  \u001b[56;2H Note: You cannot use both \"mb_output_handler\" with \"ob_iconv_handler\"\r\n;   and you cannot use both \"ob_gzhandler\" and \"zlib.output_compression\".\r\n; Note: output_handler must be empty if this is set 'On' !!!!\r\n;   Instead you must use zlib.output_handler.\r\n; https://php.net/output-handler\u001b[61;2Houtput_handler =  \r\n\u001b[19X\u001b[63;2H URL rewriter function rewrites URL on the fly by using\r\n; output buffer. You can set tar\u001b[30m\u001b[103mget\u001b[m\u000f tags by this configuration.\r\n; \"form\" tag is special tag. It will add hidden input tag to pass values.\u001b[66;223H\u001b[0;10;7m\u000f213,9           \u001b[67;5H\u001b[?25h"]
[0.025, "o", "\u001b[?25l\b\u001b[m\u000f \b"]
[0.004, "o", "\u001b[1;65r\u001b[H\u001b[33L\u001b[1;67r\u001b[H;   Default Value: \"EGPCS\"\u001b[K\r\n;   Development Value: \"GPCS\"\u001b[K\r\n;   Production Value: \"GPCS\"\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; zend.assertions\u001b[K\r\n;   Default Value: 1\u001b[K\r\n;   Development Value: 1\u001b[K\r\n;   Production Value: -1\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; zend.exception_ignore_args\u001b[K\r\n;   Default Value: Off\u001b[K\r\n;   Development Value: Off\u001b[K\r\n;   Production Value: On\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; zend.exception_string_param_max_len\u001b[K\r\n;   Default Value: 15\u001b[K\r\n;   Development Value: 15\u001b[K\r\n;   Production Value: 0\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;\u001b[K\r\n; php.ini Options  ;\u001b[K\r\n;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;\u001b[K\r\n; Name for user-defined php.ini (.htaccess) files. Default is \".user.ini\"\u001b[K\r\n;user_ini.filename = \".user.ini\"\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; To disable this feature set this option to an empty value\u001b[K\r\n;user_ini.filename =\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n; TTL for user-defined php.ini files (time-to-live) in seconds. Default is 300 seconds (5 minutes)\u001b[K\r\n;user_ini.cache_ttl = 300\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\n;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;\u001b[K\r\n; Langua\u001b[30m\u001b[103mge\u001b[m\u000f Options ;\u001b[K\u001b[36;34H\u001b[30m\u001b[103mge\u001b[42;3Hge\u001b[43;64Hge\u001b[66;223H\u001b[0;10;7m\u000f180,9           8\u001b[67;4H\u001b[?25h"]
[0.026, "o", "\u001b[?25l\b\u001b[m\u000f \b"]
[0.004, "o", "\u001b[66AThe value can be a strin\u001b[30m\u001b[103mg\u001b[m\u000f, a number, a PHP constant (e.\u001b[30m\u001b[103mg\u001b[m\u000f. E_ALL or M_PI), one\u001b[2;3Hof the INI constants (On, Off, True, False, Yes, No and None) or an expression\u001b[3;3H(e.\u001b[30m\u001b[103mg\u001b[m\u000f. E_ALL & ~E_NOTICE), a quoted strin\u001b[30m\u001b[103mg\u001b[m\u000f (\"bar\"), or a reference to a\r\n; previously set variable or directive (e.\u001b[30m\u001b[103mg\u001b[m\u000f. ${foo})\r\n\u001b[17X\u001b[6;3HExpressions in the INI file are limited to bitwise operators and parentheses:\u001b[7;3H|  bitwise OR\u001b[9X\u001b[8;3H^  bitwise XOR\u001b[8X\r\n; &  bitwise AND\u001b[10;3H~  bitwise NOT\u001b[12X\u001b[11;3H!  boolean NOT\u001b[6X\r\n\u001b[26X\u001b[13;3HBoolean fla\u001b[30m\u001b[103mg\u001b[m\u000fs can be turned on usin\u001b[30m\u001b[103mg\u001b[m\u000f the values 1, On, True or Yes.\r\n; They can be turned off usin\u001b[30m\u001b[103mg\u001b[m\u000f the values 0, Off, False or No.\r\n\u001b[37X\u001b[16;3HAn empty strin\u001b[30m\u001b[103mg\u001b[m\u000f can be denoted by simply not writin\u001b[30m\u001b[103mg\u001b[m\u000f anythin\u001b[30m\u001b[103mg\u001b[m\u000f after the equal\u001b[17;3Hsi\u001b[30m\u001b[103mg\u001b[m\u000fn, or by usin\u001b[30m\u001b[103mg\u001b[m\u000f the None keyword:\r\n\u001b[23X\n; foo =         ; sets foo to an empty strin\u001b[30m\u001b[103mg\u001b[20;2H\u001b[m\u000f foo = None    ; sets foo to an empty strin\u001b[30m\u001b[103mg\u001b[21;3H\u001b[m\u000ffoo = \"None\"  ; sets foo to the strin\u001b[30m\u001b[103mg\u001b[m\u000f 'None'\r\n\u001b[20X\u001b[23;3HIf you use constants in your value, and these constants belon\u001b[30m\u001b[103mg\u001b[m\u000f to a    \u001b[24;2H dynamically loaded extension (either a PHP extension or a Zend extension),\r\n; you may only use these constants *after* the line that loads the extension.\r\n\u001b[59X\u001b[27;2H;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;; \r\n; About this file ;\u001b[29;2H;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;\u001b[79X\u001b[30;2H PHP comes packa\u001b[30m\u001b[103mg\u001b[m\u000fed with two INI files. One that is recommended to be used\r\n; in production environments and one that is recommended to be used in\u001b[32;2H development environments.\r\n\u001b[20X\u001b[34;2H php.ini-production contains settin\u001b[30m\u001b[103mg\u001b[m\u000fs which hold security, performance and\r\n; best practices at its core. But please be aware, these settin\u001b[30m\u001b[103mg\u001b[m\u000fs may break\u001b[36;3Hcompatibility with older or less security-conscious applications. We\u001b[37;3Hrecommendin\u001b[30m\u001b[103mg\u001b[m\u000f usin\u001b[30m\u001b[103mg\u001b[m\u000f the production ini in production and testin\u001b[30m\u001b[103mg\u001b[m\u000f environments.\r\n\u001b[11X\n; php.ini-development is very similar to its production variant, except it is\u001b[40;3Hmuch more verbose when it comes to errors. We recommend usin\u001b[30m\u001b[103mg\u001b[m\u000f the\u001b[7X\u001b[41;3Hdevelopment version only in development environments, as errors shown to\u001b[42;3Happlication users can inadvertently leak otherwise secure information.\u001b[6X\r\n\u001b[77X\u001b[44;3HThis is the php.ini-production INI file.\u001b[37X\r\n\u001b[79X\u001b[46;2H;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;\u001b[17X\u001b[47;3HQuick Reference ;\u001b[48;2H;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;;\u001b[5X\r\n\u001b[23X\u001b[50;3HThe followin\u001b[30m\u001b[103mg\u001b[m\u000f are all the settin\u001b[30m\u001b[103mg\u001b[m\u000fs which are different in either the production\r\n; or development versions of the INIs with respect to PHP's default behavior.\r\n; Please see the actual settin\u001b[30m\u001b[103mg\u001b[m\u000fs later in the document for more details as to why\u001b[53;3Hwe recommend these chan\u001b[30m\u001b[103mg\u001b[m\u000fes in PHP's behavior.\u001b[24X\r\n\u001b[27X\n; display_errors\r\n;   Default Value: On\u001b[57;3H  Development Value: On\u001b[45X\u001b[58;3H  Production Value: Off\u001b[55X\r\n\u001b[76X\u001b[60;3Hdisplay_startup_errors\u001b[40X\u001b[61;3H  Default Value: On\u001b[56X\u001b[62;3H  Development Value: On\u001b[47X\u001b[63;3H  Production Value: Off\u001b[53X\r\n\u001b[80X\u001b[65;4Hrror_reportin\u001b[30m\u001b[103mg\u001b[m\u000f\u001b[61X\u001b[66;224H\u001b[0;10;7m\u000f07,17          2\u001b[67;3H\u001b[?25h"]
[0.030, "o", "\u001b[?25l\b\u001b[m\u000f \u001b[1;65r\u001b[H\u001b[6L\u001b[1;67r\u001b[H; directive = value\u001b[K\r\n; Directive names are *case sensitive* - foo=bar is different from FOO=bar.\u001b[K\r\n; Directives are variables used to configure PHP or PHP extensions.\u001b[K\r\n; There is no name validation.  If PHP can't find an expected\u001b[K\r\n; directive because it is not set or is mistyped, a default value will be used.\u001b[K\r\n\u001b[K\u001b[7;27Hg, a number, a PHP constant (e.g\u001b[9;6Hg. E_ALL & ~E_NOTICE), a quoted string\u001b[10;43Hg\u001b[19;14Hgs can be turned on using\u001b[20;30Hg\u001b[22;17Hg can be denoted by simply not writing anything\u001b[23;5Hgn, or by using\u001b[25;45Hg\u001b[26;45Hg\u001b[27;40Hg\u001b[29;64Hg\u001b[36;18Hg\u001b[40;37Hg\u001b[41;64Hg\u001b[43;14Hg using the production ini in production and testing\u001b[46;63Hg\u001b[56;15Hg are all the setting\u001b[58;31Hg\u001b[59;26Hg\u001b[66;225H\u001b[0;10;7m\u000f1,0-1         1\u001b[67;2H\u001b[?25h"]
